    "client_msg_id": "1e718920-3220-44eb-8861-50326ebf3737",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "I am back with Wasp weekly updates! I will try to do them every week from now on, as a sort of accountability mechanism. This one covers last couple of weeks:\n- Added support for newest, production-ready version of Prisma.\n- Added support for .env file.\n- PostgreSQL can now be used during development.\n- Moved CI from Travis &amp; Appveyor to Github Actions -&gt; it is faster, simpler and free.\nPlan for this week:\n- Looking into automatic CHANGELOG generation -&gt; still figuring out how to set it up. <http://conventionalcommits.org|conventionalcommits.org> seems like the way to go.\n- Implement note taking app in Wasp as a case study.\n- Write and publish a blog post.",
    "user": "UUB7RA7PF",
    "ts": "1619520756.052300",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
